title: Alabama Cycling Classic presents Sunny King Criterium
description: Alabama Cycling Classic presents the Sunny King Criterium.  This year's event features the same great course, and experience that riders have grown to love.
registration: Online registration is through USA Cycling.  On-site registration is available until 20 minutes before the race takes place.

title: Alabama Cycling Classic Presents McClellan RR
description: The Alabama Cycling Classic presents the Ft. McClellan Road Race again for 2017.
registration: Online registration through USA Cycling.  No day-of registration allowed for this event.

title: Tour de Bay Criterium
description: Tour de Bay is the 2017 Alabama State Criterium Championship.  All riders are eligible for cash payouts in their categories, but only riders from the state of Alabama are eligible for the state championship medals.  This flier will be replaced shortly, and it will include the cash payouts for the various groups.
course: Course is slightly modified over previous years, but has brand new pavement, and the course is an 8 corner "T" shaped layout in the heart of downtown Mobile.
registration: Online registration is available at USA Cycling.
notes: USA Cycling rules apply.  Wheel pit is a wheel-in/wheel-out pit, so riders will need to provide their own spare wheels for the pit.
directions: The Start/Finish will be at Dauphin/Cedar, across from Wintzell’s Oyster House – about ½ mile west of last year’s location

title: Tour de Bay Fondo
description: Fun ride that starts and finishes in downtown Mobile
course: Course info, with links to maps will be added to the flier update that is coming to replace this.

title: Joe Davis Crit Series
description: New crit series in Huntsville that will feature the USA Cycling Beginner Racer Program
course: Course is a 4 corner course that goes through a parking lot at
registration:
Series registration for both the Beginner Clinic and the Crit Series will be open until May 17th.  From that point, we will only offer registration for each event.  The Registration for each event will be online only, and we will leave this open until 20 minutes before each race on the day of the event.  

The prices are $15 for early registration for weeknight events, but will go up to $20 the day-of the event.  If you are eligible to race multiple races, then you can register for the second event for just $5.

The weekend events will feature a different format, and entry fees will be a little higher to cover expenses.  The entry fees will be $20 for early pre-reg, then go up to $25 the week of the event.  Registration will go up to $30 the day of the event.
notes: USA Cycling rules apply.  Wheel pit will be in wheel in/wheel out.  Free lap will be available until 8 K to go in the race.

title: AL State TT and TTT Championship
description: The AL State TT Championship returns to Columbiana again for 2017.  The courses will be the same as years past.
course: Rolling course in the Columbiana area. Only a few corners, with winding roads and a few short climbs. Good pavement, and low traffic. Course maps found for both courses at the following links: Long Course- http://www.strava.com/segments/1641877 Short Course- http://www.strava.com/routes/708196
registration:
Online registration ONLY for this event.  Riders must register by the close of online registration on August 17th. 

For Team Time Trial, one person registers the team and lets us know at the event who will be riding with the team.
notes:
USA Cycling rules apply.  Riders must hold a USA Cycling annual license holder to be eligible for the state championship.  Start lists will be emailed, and posted online for all riders to view on Friday, August 18th.  

For the 2 person TTT, the finish time is the time of the second rider, so you must finish both riders.  For the 4 person TTT, your time is based on the third rider to cross the line, so you must at least finish with 3 riders.
directions: Start location and packet pick-up is at: 222 Joinertown Rd, Columbiana, AL 35051

title: Standard Deluxe Dirt Road Century
description: Are you ready for 100 miles of smooth, flowing, red, dirt roads? Waverly, Alabama is home to some of the most highly concentrated dirt roads in Alabama. Starting at the folksy Standard Deluxe music venue, we will be cruising a 100 and 60 mile loop during a self-supported dirt road race. Whether you are just looking to finish this adventure or crush the competition, come on out and join us.
course:
What bike should I ride?

A cross bike with about 40c tires works well, so does a skinny tired hardtail mountain bike.

 

What are the roads like?

Awesome. Smooth. Sometimes a little chunky. About 80% dirt/gravel.
registration: Online and Day of Registration Available
notes: The 100 and 60 miles races will be timed, with custom awards being presented to the top 3 male/female finishers. The 30 miles ride will be a fun event, designed to give folks an idea of what the Standard Deluxe Rides are all about. No awards or timing will be presented for the 30 mile edition, as it is non-competitive in nature.
directions:
Start/Finish will be at the Standard Deluxe at 1015 Mayberry Ave, Waverly, AL 36879.

Camping for Friday/Saturday evening will be available for $5/ racer 

*** Details are subject to change, check out website for updates!*** 
http://www.terrafirmacycling.com/standard-deluxe-dirt-road-century-1/
